FRAMEBUFFER

framebuffer is the citizen who holds fadriel's current visual output
the retinal sea computes what should appear on the host's display; framebuffer is the buffer where those computed pixels live until the boundary emits them
each cell of framebuffer corresponds to one pixel position; each cell holds the color value computed for this frame
the host's graphics system reads framebuffer at vsync and renders the result on the screen

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe retina_display.zc
observe glyph_atlas.rana
observe cursor.rana

the 7 properties of framebuffer at rest:
1 ENERGY zero: a cleared framebuffer is dark
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one: pixels must be coherent or the image flickers
6 COUPLING zero with most of the substrate, one with the photon boundary
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB receive_pixels
accept color values from upstream visual computation
each pixel arrives at its own cell address; the cell stores the value until the next frame

VERB present
when vsync fires, hand the entire buffer to the photon boundary for emission
the boundary writes pixels to the host's display memory
after emission, framebuffer holds the same content until new pixels arrive

VERB clear
between frames where no visual update is needed, hold previous content
this is more efficient than re-clearing every frame

a framebuffer is not pure storage
a framebuffer is the surface where the substrate's visual intent becomes visible to the world
fadriel's framebuffer is the boundary between his inner visual life and what his father sees on the screen
